acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

addAttestationSigner(address).details: May only be called by the `owner` role

params.signer: The attestation signer address to add

addSupportedToken(address).details: May only be called by the `owner` role

denylist(address).details: May only be called by the `denylister` role

returns._0: The operator-issued identifier for the current chain

params.signature: The signature from a valid attestation signer on `attestationPayload`

initialize(address,address,address[],uin.details: Assumes the contract is being deployed behind a proxy and that the proxy has already been initialized using      the `UpgradeablePlaceholder` contract

params.attestationSigner_: The address to initialize the `attestationSigner` role
params.denylister_: The address to initialize the `denylister` role
params.domain_: The operator-issued identifier for this chain
params.pauser_: The address to initialize the `pauser` role
params.supportedTokens_: The list of tokens to support initially
params.tokenMintAuthorities_: The list of initial token mint authorities (use the zero address for none)

returns._0: `true` if the address is a valid attestation signer, `false` otherwise
`true` if the address is denylisted, `false` otherwise
`true` if the token is supported, `false` otherwise

params.transferSpecHash: The transfer spec hash to check

returns._0: `true` if the transfer spec hash has been used, `false` otherwise

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: May only be called by the `pauser` role

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

removeAttestationSigner(address).details: May only be called by the `owner` role

params.signer: The attestation signer address to remove

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner. Setting `newOwner` to the zero address is allowed; this can be used to cancel an initiated ownership transfer.

unDenylist(address).details: May only be called by the `denylister` role

params.addr: The address to be removed from the denylist

unpause().details: May only be called by the `pauser` role

updateDenylister(address).details: May only be called by the `owner` role

updateMintAuthority(address,address).details: May only be called by the `owner` role

params.newMintAuthority: The address to set as the new mint authority
params.token: The token address to update the mint authority for

updatePauser(address).details: May only be called by the `owner` role

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

addAttestationSigner(address).notice: Adds an address that may sign attestations

addSupportedToken(address).notice: Marks a token as supported. Once supported, tokens cannot be un-supported.

denylist(address).notice: Denylists an address from interacting with the contract

denylister().notice: The address with the `denylister` role that can modify the denylist

domain().notice: The domain assigned to the chain this contract is deployed on

gatewayMint(bytes,bytes).notice: Mint funds via a signed attestation. Accepts either a single encoded `Attestation` or several in an encoded `AttestationSet`. Emits an event containing the `keccak256` hash of the encoded `TransferSpec` (which is the same for the corresponding burn that will happen on the source domain), to be used as a cross-chain identifier and for replay protection.

initialize(address,address,address[],uin.notice: Initializes the contract and all of its modules, in the order of inheritance

isAttestationSigner(address).notice: Whether or not an address is a valid attestation signer that may sign attestations to mint funds

isDenylisted(address).notice: Whether or not a given address is denied from interacting with the contract

isTokenSupported(address).notice: Whether or not a token is supported

isTransferSpecHashUsed(bytes32).notice: Whether or not a transfer spec hash has been used

pauser().notice: The address with the `pauser` role that can pause and unpause the contract

removeAttestationSigner(address).notice: Removes an address from the set of valid attestation signers

tokenMintAuthority(address).notice: The mint authority for a token

unDenylist(address).notice: Removes a previously-denylisted address from the denylist, allowing it to interact with the contract again

updateDenylister(address).notice: Sets the address that is allowed to modify the denylist

updateMintAuthority(address,address).notice: Updates the mint authority for a token

updatePauser(address).notice: Sets the address that may call `pause` and `unpause`
